Specpr help facility is built around key words and manual sections.
To get help on a particular topic, type the command:

              help keyword


 Keyword                 Topic

bugs        4.4 Bug Reports
cmd         2.4 Command Interpretation
locks       4.2 Protective Locks (on specpr files)
protection  2.3 File Protection
    1       Specpr Chapter 1: INTRODUCTION
    2       Specpr Chapter 2: PROGRAM STRUCTURE
    3       Specpr Chapter 3: STARTING SPECPR ON UNIX
    4       Specpr Chapter 4: IMPORTANT RULES
    5       Specpr Chapter 5: PROGRAM INITIALIZATION
    6       Specpr Chapter  :DEVICE AND FILE ASSIGNMENTS
    7       Specpr Chapter  :MAIN MENU: PROGRAM OPERATIONS CONTROL
    8       Specpr Chapter  :MATH OPERATIONS
    9       Specpr Chapter  :CRT PLOT ROUTINES
    10      Specpr Chapter  :DATA DISPLAY, TRANSFER, AND OVERLAY
    11      Specpr Chapter  :DATA FILE LIST
    12      Specpr Chapter  :EXTINCTION ROUTINES
    13      Specpr Chapter  :PLOTTING ROUTINES FOR WORK AND PUBLICATION
    14      Specpr Chapter  :HELP
    15      Specpr Chapter  :SPECPR STANDARD FORMAT OF DATA FILES
 
    f1      Description of all SPECIAL functions
    fn      (where n is an integer) gives help on special function n
            For example: f20 gives help on special function 20.
